<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
			
    <p n="1">
        Prosperity! Fortune!
    </p>
    
    <p n="1-3">
        3rd year of the king Parakesarivarman.
    </p>
    
    <p n="3-16">
        So that there be <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āka</foreign></supplied>,
        <supplied reason="subaudible">from the land</supplied>, which I, Kaṟṟaḷi Piccaṉ of Tiruvāṭutuṟai have bought in Ciṟṟāṉaiccūr,
        <list>
            <item>where it reaches to the north in Mēṟpulam / in the western rice field, six <foreign>mā</foreign>s for one person singing the <foreign>tiruppatiyam</foreign>,</item>
            <item>where it reaches south of this, one quarter ... for the one who supplies <supplied reason="subaudible">liquids for</supplied> the glorious bath,</item>
            <item>and, where it reaches south of this, one quarter ... for the glorious drummer,</item>
        </list>
        
        I have made and given a permanent endowment, I, Kaṟṟaḷi Piccaṉ.
        
    </p>
    
    <p n="16-17">
        This <supplied reason="subaudible">is under</supplied> the protection of the many great devotees of Śiva.
    </p>
</div>
    
